## Backend Architecture

### [app.py](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/app.py) — FastAPI Entry Point
- **App name**: `PattaFlow`
- **Middleware**: Per-request UUID logging (`X-Request-ID` header), CORS (all origins)
- **Static mounts**: `/files` → `outputs/`, `/input-files` → `inputs/`
- **Versioned router**: All endpoints under `/api/v1/`

#### API Endpoints

| Method | Path | Handler | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|---------|
| GET | `/api/v1/health` | inline | Health check |
| POST | `/api/v1/validate` | [handle_validate](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/handler.py#554-740) | Main workflow: EC + Sale Deed validation (streaming NDJSON) |
| POST | `/api/v1/validate-single-doc` | [handle_validate_single](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/handler.py#854-912) | Re-validate a single document on demand |
| POST | `/api/v1/download-ec` | `handle_download_ec` | Download EC PDF from TNGIS |
| POST | `/api/v1/getlandinfo` | [handle_get_land_info](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/getlandinfo/handler.py#147-150) | Get land info by lat/lng |
| POST | `/api/v1/verify-supporting-doc` | [handle_verify_supporting_doc](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/handler.py#741-761) | Verify supporting doc (Aadhaar etc.) against deed |
| POST | `/api/v1/chat-with-doc` | [handle_chat_with_doc](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/handler.py#814-853) | AI chat about a specific document |
| POST | `/api/v1/save-node-note` | `handle_save_node_note` | Save collaborative note for a deed node |
| GET | `/api/v1/get-node-notes` | `handle_get_node_notes` | Retrieve all node notes |
| GET | `/api/v1/get-validation-results/{id}` | inline | Fetch cached validation results by request ID |
| GET | `/api/v1/get-global-hierarchy/{id}` | [handle_get_global_hierarchy](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/handler.py#982-996) | Get full hierarchy as ReactFlow data |
| POST | `/api/v1/search-survey-timeline` | [handle_search_survey_timeline](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/handler.py#997-1014) | Search for a specific survey number's lineage |

