### Core Validation Pipeline (`api/validate/`)

The main workflow is a **5-stage generator pipeline** that streams progress events to the frontend:

```
EC PDF + Sale Deed ZIP/Dir
         │
    ┌────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐
    │  Stage 1: EC Extraction (ECProcessor)    │
    │  • pypdf text extraction in chunks       │
    │  • Gemini (flash-lite) parses each chunk │
    │  • Outputs: ec_raw_full.txt, ec_final.json│
    └────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
         │
    ┌────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐
    │  Stage 2: Document Matching              │
    │  (DocumentMatcher)                       │
    │  • Normalizes doc numbers (lower + _-/)  │
    │  • Matches EC entries → PDF filenames    │
    │  • Sorts by date, fills quota (limit)    │
    │  • Copies matched PDFs to workspace      │
    │  • Persists to global vault              │
    └────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
         │
    ┌────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐
    │  Stage 3: Sale Deed Metadata Extraction  │
    │  (SaleDeedProcessor)                     │
    │  • Uploads each PDF to Gemini Flash      │
    │  • Prompt extracts: parties, survey no,  │
    │    extent, dates, supporting docs, IDs   │
    │  • Outputs: <docno>_metadata.txt files   │
    │  • ≥10 docs → ThreadPoolExecutor (3)     │
    └────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
         │
    ┌────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐
    │  Stage 3.5: Hierarchy Generation         │
    │  (HierarchyGenerator)                    │
    │  • Extract text from EC PDF              │
    │  • Gemini (flash) → nested JSON tree     │
    │  • Repair: flatten → group by SN → link  │
    │    by prefix rules (46 → 46/1 → 46/1A)  │
    │  • Generate: hierarchy_tree.json         │
    │             hierarchy_view.html (Mermaid)│
    │  • Build ReactFlow nodes + edges         │
    └────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
         │
    ┌────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐
    │  Stage 4: Validation (Validator)         │
    │  • For each matched doc:                 │
    │    - Look up EC entry by doc number      │
    │    - Read <docno>_metadata.txt           │
    │    - Gemini (flash-lite) forensic audit  │
    │    - Returns: match, comparisons, score  │
    │  • ≥10 docs → ThreadPoolExecutor (3)     │
    │  • Outputs: <docno>_validation.json,     │
    │             results.json                 │
    └────▼─────────────────────────────────────┘
         │
    Final result JSON → Frontend
```

#### Event Stream Format (NDJSON)
Each line is a JSON object with `type`:
- `step_start` / `step_complete` → pipeline stage progress
- [log](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/handler.py#59-78) → major message
- [sub_log](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/handler.py#59-78) → granular detail within a step
- [result](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/app.py#242-255) → final data payload
- `error` → failure notification

---

### [ECProcessor](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/ec_processor.py#10-134) ([ec_processor.py](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/ec_processor.py))
- Splits PDF into chunks of `CHUNK_SIZE` pages (env var, default 8)
- Each chunk → Gemini with `RAW_PROMPT` → structured text blocks
- Blocks parsed via regex: `--- TRANSACTION START/END ---` markers
- Fields: doc number, date, nature, sellers, buyers, survey_no, extent
- Caches result in `ec_final.json` (skips re-processing if found)

### [DocumentMatcher](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/matcher.py#11-175) ([matcher.py](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/matcher.py))
- **Normalization**: lowercase + replace `-`, `/`, space with `_`
- **Sorting**: newest-first by date (format: `24-Jul-1985`)
- **Deduplication**: skips already-seen document numbers
- **Quota filling**: iterates through history to find N matched files
- **Workspace**: copies matched PDFs to a tmp workspace; persists to `outputs/storage/vault/`

### [SaleDeedProcessor](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/sale_deed_processor.py#6-48) ([sale_deed_processor.py](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/sale_deed_processor.py))
- Uploads PDF to Gemini using [generate_from_file](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/common/gemini_helper.py#52-99)
- Uses `SALE_DEED_PROMPT` (extracts Tamil/English metadata)
- Caches output in `<filename>_metadata.txt`

### [HierarchyGenerator](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/hierarchy_generator.py#10-779) ([hierarchy_generator.py](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/hierarchy_generator.py))
- **LLM Extraction**: Full EC text → `HIERARCHY_PROMPT` → nested JSON tree
- **Survey Number Hierarchy Logic**: `46` → `46/1` → `46/1A` → `46/1A1` (prefix-based)
- **Repair**: flattens, infers orphaned SNs from neighbors, re-groups, sorts chronologically
- **Outputs**:
  1. `hierarchy_tree.json` — raw tree
  2. `hierarchy_view.html` — static Mermaid.js interactive visualization
  3. ReactFlow JSON ([nodes](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/hierarchy_generator.py#244-283) + `edges`) for the React frontend
- **Search**: [find_survey_timeline()](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/hierarchy_generator.py#645-744) for filtering by specific survey number + limit

### [Validator](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/validator.py#10-209) ([validator.py](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/validator.py))
- [validate()](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/validator.py#38-72) → generator yielding progress messages
- [validate_single_doc()](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/validator.py#73-209) → validates one doc (used for parallel execution + on-demand)
- Sends EC JSON + deed metadata to [construct_validation_prompt()](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/prompts/validation_prompts.py#3-154) → Gemini
- Response parsed for: [match](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/matcher.py#79-165) (bool), `trustability_score`, `comparisons[]`
- `VisualDebugger` triggered on NOT MATCHED fields (if `visual_debug=True`)
- Output paths mapped relative to server mounts for frontend URLs

### [SupportingVerifier](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/supporting_verifier.py#10-61) ([supporting_verifier.py](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/validate/supporting_verifier.py))
- Takes supporting PDF (Aadhaar, PAN, Death Certificate)
- Renders page 1 as image using PyMuPDF → uploads to Gemini Flash
- Verifies the identity doc matches deed parties

### [ECDownloader](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/download_ec/ec_downloader.py#6-106) ([ec_downloader.py](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/api/download_ec/ec_downloader.py))
- Hits `https://tngis.tn.gov.in` TNGIS API
- CSRF (XSRF-TOKEN) handling via session cookies
- Decodes Base64 EC PDF and saves locally

### [GeminiHelper](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/common/gemini_helper.py#10-99) ([common/gemini_helper.py](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/common/gemini_helper.py))
- Wraps `google.genai` client
- Two modes: [generate_from_text](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/common/gemini_helper.py#24-51) (text prompt) and [generate_from_file](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/common/gemini_helper.py#52-99) (PDF/image upload)
- Retry logic: 3 attempts with exponential backoff on 503/overloaded errors
- `temperature=0.0`, `top_p=0.1` for maximum determinism

