## LLM Prompts

| File | Prompt | Model Used | Purpose |
|------|--------|-----------|---------|
| [ec_prompts.py](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/prompts/ec_prompts.py) | `RAW_PROMPT` | flash-lite | Extract raw transactions from EC page chunks |
| [sale_deed_prompts.py](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/prompts/sale_deed_prompts.py) | `SALE_DEED_PROMPT` | flash | Full metadata from a sale deed PDF |
| [hierarchy_prompts.py](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/prompts/hierarchy_prompts.py) | `HIERARCHY_PROMPT` | flash | Build nested tree JSON from EC text |
| [validation_prompts.py](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/prompts/validation_prompts.py) | [construct_validation_prompt()](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/prompts/validation_prompts.py#3-154) | flash-lite | Forensic audit: EC vs deed metadata |
| [supporting_prompts.py](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Server/prompts/supporting_prompts.py) | `SUPPORTING_DOC_VERIFICATION_PROMPT` | flash | Verify supporting identity documents |

### Validation Prompt Rules (Key Design Decisions)
The validation prompt is the most critical. It uses **8 validation rules**:
1. **Doc Number** — exact match (format differences OK)
2. **Date** — same calendar date (format differences OK)
3. **Names** — phonetic + initial expansion allowed; Power-of-Attorney mappings valid
4. **Kinship** — supplemental info (EC empty + deed has kinship) = MATCHED, direct contradiction = NOT MATCHED
5. **Nature** — synonyms accepted (e.g., "Conveyance Non Metro/UA" = "Sale Deed")
6. **Survey Number** — exact or overlap match
7. **Extent** — within ±5-10% = MATCHED (REASONABLE); unit conversions valid
8. **Supporting Docs** — checks Aadhaar/PAN/Voter ID for parties; Death Certificate required for partition deeds

