## Frontend Architecture

### Pages

| Route | Component | Purpose |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| `/` | [LandingPage](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Client/src/pages/LandingPage.tsx#5-65) | Entry point: routes to Map or Verify |
| `/verify` | [Index](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Client/src/pages/Index.tsx#4-55) | Document upload and batch validation |
| `/map` | [MapPage](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Client/src/pages/MapPage.tsx#6-52) | Interactive map + land info + EC download |
| `/hierarchy` | [HierarchyPage](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Client/src/pages/HierarchyPage.tsx#19-808) | ReactFlow hierarchy, PDF preview, AI chat |

### Key Components

| Component | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| [UploadForm](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Client/src/components/UploadForm.tsx#37-473) | Main form: file upload / local path, streaming reader, result display |
| `StreamingMessages` | Real-time NDJSON stream log + step progress bar |
| `ValidationResults` | Grid display of per-document validation results |
| `ValidationResultItem` | Single document result card with comparisons |
| `ReactFlowHierarchy` | Interactive ReactFlow canvas with custom nodes and edge types |
| [HierarchyPage](file:///d:/Master_legal_AI/Client/src/pages/HierarchyPage.tsx#19-808) | Full-page view: ReactFlow + resizable panel + PDF preview + chat |
| `DocChat` | AI chat interface for a selected document |
| `PdfAnnotator` | PDF viewer with highlight/annotation support (react-pdf-highlighter) |
| `SurveyTimeline` | Timeline view within the hierarchy page |
| `TrustabilityScore` | Visual trustability gauge for validated docs |
| `FileDropZone` | Drag-and-drop file input |
| `map/MapView` | OpenLayers map component |
| `map/InfoSidebar` | Sidebar shown on map click: land info + EC download |
| `map/Navbar` | Map page navigation bar |

### HierarchyPage Data Flow
1. Reads `requestId` + `surveyNumber` query params
2. If `surveyNumber` → `POST /search-survey-timeline` (filtered view)
3. Else → `GET /get-global-hierarchy/{id}` (full tree)
4. Fetches `GET /get-validation-results/{id}` in parallel
5. Fetches `GET /get-node-notes` and merges into node data
6. On node click: opens resizable panel with metadata summary + PDF + validation
7. Supports: collaborative notes (auto-saved), supporting doc upload/verify, single-doc re-audit, PDF annotations, AI chat

